6971:Drivers/STM32G4xx_HAL_Driver/Inc/stm32g4xx_ll_adc.h **** /**
6972:Drivers/STM32G4xx_HAL_Driver/Inc/stm32g4xx_ll_adc.h ****   * @brief  Set ADC analog watchdog threshold value of threshold
6973:Drivers/STM32G4xx_HAL_Driver/Inc/stm32g4xx_ll_adc.h ****   *         high or low.
6974:Drivers/STM32G4xx_HAL_Driver/Inc/stm32g4xx_ll_adc.h ****   * @note   If values of both thresholds high or low must be set,
6975:Drivers/STM32G4xx_HAL_Driver/Inc/stm32g4xx_ll_adc.h ****   *         use function @ref LL_ADC_ConfigAnalogWDThresholds().
6976:Drivers/STM32G4xx_HAL_Driver/Inc/stm32g4xx_ll_adc.h ****   * @note   In case of ADC resolution different of 12 bits,
6977:Drivers/STM32G4xx_HAL_Driver/Inc/stm32g4xx_ll_adc.h ****   *         analog watchdog thresholds data require a specific shift.
6978:Drivers/STM32G4xx_HAL_Driver/Inc/stm32g4xx_ll_adc.h ****   *         Use helper macro @ref __LL_ADC_ANALOGWD_SET_THRESHOLD_RESOLUTION().
6979:Drivers/STM32G4xx_HAL_Driver/Inc/stm32g4xx_ll_adc.h ****   * @note   On this STM32 series, there are 2 kinds of analog watchdog
6980:Drivers/STM32G4xx_HAL_Driver/Inc/stm32g4xx_ll_adc.h ****   *         instance:
6981:Drivers/STM32G4xx_HAL_Driver/Inc/stm32g4xx_ll_adc.h ****   *         - AWD standard (instance AWD1):
6982:Drivers/STM32G4xx_HAL_Driver/Inc/stm32g4xx_ll_adc.h ****   *           - channels monitored: can monitor 1 channel or all channels.
6983:Drivers/STM32G4xx_HAL_Driver/Inc/stm32g4xx_ll_adc.h ****   *           - groups monitored: ADC groups regular and-or injected.
6984:Drivers/STM32G4xx_HAL_Driver/Inc/stm32g4xx_ll_adc.h ****   *           - resolution: resolution is not limited (corresponds to
6985:Drivers/STM32G4xx_HAL_Driver/Inc/stm32g4xx_ll_adc.h ****   *             ADC resolution configured).
6986:Drivers/STM32G4xx_HAL_Driver/Inc/stm32g4xx_ll_adc.h ****   *         - AWD flexible (instances AWD2, AWD3):
6987:Drivers/STM32G4xx_HAL_Driver/Inc/stm32g4xx_ll_adc.h ****   *           - channels monitored: flexible on channels monitored, selection is
6988:Drivers/STM32G4xx_HAL_Driver/Inc/stm32g4xx_ll_adc.h ****   *             channel wise, from from 1 to all channels.
6989:Drivers/STM32G4xx_HAL_Driver/Inc/stm32g4xx_ll_adc.h ****   *             Specificity of this analog watchdog: Multiple channels can
6990:Drivers/STM32G4xx_HAL_Driver/Inc/stm32g4xx_ll_adc.h ****   *             be selected. For example:
6991:Drivers/STM32G4xx_HAL_Driver/Inc/stm32g4xx_ll_adc.h ****   *             (LL_ADC_AWD_CHANNEL4_REG_INJ | LL_ADC_AWD_CHANNEL5_REG_INJ | ...)
6992:Drivers/STM32G4xx_HAL_Driver/Inc/stm32g4xx_ll_adc.h ****   *           - groups monitored: not selection possible (monitoring on both
6993:Drivers/STM32G4xx_HAL_Driver/Inc/stm32g4xx_ll_adc.h ****   *             groups regular and injected).
6994:Drivers/STM32G4xx_HAL_Driver/Inc/stm32g4xx_ll_adc.h ****   *             Channels selected are monitored on groups regular and injected:
6995:Drivers/STM32G4xx_HAL_Driver/Inc/stm32g4xx_ll_adc.h ****   *             LL_ADC_AWD_CHANNELxx_REG_INJ (do not use parameters
6996:Drivers/STM32G4xx_HAL_Driver/Inc/stm32g4xx_ll_adc.h ****   *             LL_ADC_AWD_CHANNELxx_REG and LL_ADC_AWD_CHANNELxx_INJ)
6997:Drivers/STM32G4xx_HAL_Driver/Inc/stm32g4xx_ll_adc.h ****   *           - resolution: resolution is limited to 8 bits: if ADC resolution is
6998:Drivers/STM32G4xx_HAL_Driver/Inc/stm32g4xx_ll_adc.h ****   *             12 bits the 4 LSB are ignored, if ADC resolution is 10 bits
6999:Drivers/STM32G4xx_HAL_Driver/Inc/stm32g4xx_ll_adc.h ****   *             the 2 LSB are ignored.
7000:Drivers/STM32G4xx_HAL_Driver/Inc/stm32g4xx_ll_adc.h ****   * @note   If ADC oversampling is enabled, ADC analog watchdog thresholds are
7001:Drivers/STM32G4xx_HAL_Driver/Inc/stm32g4xx_ll_adc.h ****   *         impacted: the comparison of analog watchdog thresholds is done on
7002:Drivers/STM32G4xx_HAL_Driver/Inc/stm32g4xx_ll_adc.h ****   *         oversampling final computation (after ratio and shift application):
7003:Drivers/STM32G4xx_HAL_Driver/Inc/stm32g4xx_ll_adc.h ****   *         ADC data register bitfield [15:4] (12 most significant bits).
7004:Drivers/STM32G4xx_HAL_Driver/Inc/stm32g4xx_ll_adc.h ****   *         Examples:
7005:Drivers/STM32G4xx_HAL_Driver/Inc/stm32g4xx_ll_adc.h ****   *         - Oversampling ratio and shift selected to have ADC conversion data
7006:Drivers/STM32G4xx_HAL_Driver/Inc/stm32g4xx_ll_adc.h ****   *           on 12 bits (ratio 16 and shift 4, or ratio 32 and shift 5, ...):
7007:Drivers/STM32G4xx_HAL_Driver/Inc/stm32g4xx_ll_adc.h ****   *           ADC analog watchdog thresholds must be divided by 16.
7008:Drivers/STM32G4xx_HAL_Driver/Inc/stm32g4xx_ll_adc.h ****   *         - Oversampling ratio and shift selected to have ADC conversion data
ARM GAS  /tmp/ccnNifqE.s 			page 128


7009:Drivers/STM32G4xx_HAL_Driver/Inc/stm32g4xx_ll_adc.h ****   *           on 14 bits (ratio 16 and shift 2, or ratio 32 and shift 3, ...):
7010:Drivers/STM32G4xx_HAL_Driver/Inc/stm32g4xx_ll_adc.h ****   *           ADC analog watchdog thresholds must be divided by 4.
7011:Drivers/STM32G4xx_HAL_Driver/Inc/stm32g4xx_ll_adc.h ****   *         - Oversampling ratio and shift selected to have ADC conversion data
7012:Drivers/STM32G4xx_HAL_Driver/Inc/stm32g4xx_ll_adc.h ****   *           on 16 bits (ratio 16 and shift none, or ratio 32 and shift 1, ...):
7013:Drivers/STM32G4xx_HAL_Driver/Inc/stm32g4xx_ll_adc.h ****   *           ADC analog watchdog thresholds match directly to ADC data register.
7014:Drivers/STM32G4xx_HAL_Driver/Inc/stm32g4xx_ll_adc.h ****   * @note   On this STM32 series, setting of this feature is not conditioned to
7015:Drivers/STM32G4xx_HAL_Driver/Inc/stm32g4xx_ll_adc.h ****   *         ADC state:
7016:Drivers/STM32G4xx_HAL_Driver/Inc/stm32g4xx_ll_adc.h ****   *         ADC can be disabled, enabled with or without conversion on going
7017:Drivers/STM32G4xx_HAL_Driver/Inc/stm32g4xx_ll_adc.h ****   *         on either ADC groups regular or injected.
7018:Drivers/STM32G4xx_HAL_Driver/Inc/stm32g4xx_ll_adc.h ****   * @rmtoll TR1      HT1            LL_ADC_SetAnalogWDThresholds\n
